1
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,440
The fish are dead!

2
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:45,959
The truck. Please, Mr. Huberty.
Quickly, come on.

3
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,760
What do you know about Baal-Dahar?

4
00:04:55,119 --> 00:04:56,440
Baal-Da-what?

5
00:04:56,559 --> 00:04:59,799
l was in Jerusalem for a symposium.
Why am l here?

6
00:04:59,959 --> 00:05:04,600
Baal-Dahar`s an Arab village.
lt`s rumoured to be a terrorist base.

7
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:08,359
l should say "was."
This morning we found it destroyed.

8
00:05:08,679 --> 00:05:10,320
What does that have to do with me?

9
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:13,640
lt`s how it was destroyed.
That`s where we need your help.

10
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:18,200
My help? l know nothing about terrorists.
l think you`ve made a terrible mistake.

11
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,640
Please, come with me.

12
00:05:34,079 --> 00:05:39,000
You don`t understand. l`m the wrong man.
l can`t help you. l`m a meteorologist!

13
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:42,399
We know.
That`s why we brought you here.

14
00:05:43,239 --> 00:05:45,119
You see that...

15
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,640
...was Baal-Dahar.

16
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,679
Yesterday, a kibbutz nearby was attacked.

17
00:06:08,799 --> 00:06:12,920
They threw a petrol bomb into the school.
Thirty-four children burned to death.

18
00:06:15,079 --> 00:06:18,679
We tracked the terrorists back to here
and found this.

19
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,160
lt`s incredible.

20
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:25,760
-Can you explain it?
-lt cannot be explained.

21
00:06:30,359 --> 00:06:32,720
-l have clearance.
-You damn well better.

22
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:41,160
The Vatican.

23
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:45,040
l`m sorry...

24
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,720
...Father Lucci.

25
00:06:48,359 --> 00:06:49,760
Can you explain it?

26
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:52,440
With the proper equipment, l think--

27
00:06:52,559 --> 00:06:53,880
l don`t think so.

28
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:57,839
They`ll never explain it.

29
00:06:58,399 --> 00:07:01,839
lt`ll melt in a day or a week
and they`ll forget it.

30
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:04,600
They`ll call it a freak, an aberration.

31
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,760
You don`t think it is.

32
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:11,920
l would, Colonel, except this kind of thing
happened here once before.

33
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,600
Baal-Dahar has been here for 3,000 years.

34
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:19,200
But you see, Baal-Dahar was built
on the ruins of an older place.

35
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:21,799
A much older place.

36
00:07:22,119 --> 00:07:26,079
And it too was destroyed.
But you wouldn`t want that to explain this.

37
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,480
Why is that?

38
00:07:29,239 --> 00:07:32,200
Because that place that was destroyed
was called Sodom.

39
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,160
Destroyed by the wrath of God.

40
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,359
How`s he doing?

41
00:08:07,679 --> 00:08:11,320
l have to tell you, he`s still a boy.

42
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:16,839
-ls he kicking a lot?
-He`s very active. Moves all over the place.

43
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:21,040
That`s great. We`re getting
some good soccer in our last trimester.

44
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:25,119
l can`t wait. Two months to go.

45
00:08:25,239 --> 00:08:27,040
l want to see you next week.

46
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:30,079
l`m not completely happy with his growth.

47
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:33,159
And your amniotic fluid
is a little less than normal.

48
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:35,799
But you said he`s doing fine.

49
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:38,760
He is. There`s nothing
to be alarmed about.

50
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:42,799
But l can`t say definitely that
we won`t run into the same problem again.

51
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:47,799
l know this time it`ll be okay.
l`ve been eating really well and resting.

52
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:51,400
That`s good.
So l`ll see you both next week.

53
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,359
"...have seen the glory
Of the coming of the Lord

54
00:08:57,479 --> 00:09:01,440
"He has trampled out the vintage
Where the grapes of wrath are stored

55
00:09:01,599 --> 00:09:05,320
"He has loosed his fateful lightning
Of his terrible swift sword

56
00:09:05,479 --> 00:09:08,280
"His truth is marching on"

57
00:09:10,119 --> 00:09:12,000
They`re so adorable.

58
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,719
Would you like to see
the computer room now?

59
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:20,760
At the Oaks we start them early.

60
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,359
So your husband is a lawyer...

61
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:27,280
...and you restore fine arts
for the Hirshenson Collection.

62
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,080
-And the baby`s due...?
-February 29th.

63
00:09:32,479 --> 00:09:33,960
-lt`s leap year.
-Of course.

64
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:38,520
l notice you didn`t write anything under
"Religious Denomination."

65
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,000
Do you mind if l ask why?

66
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:45,159
Because l don`t have any.
ls that a problem?

67
00:09:45,359 --> 00:09:47,840
No, no. l just don`t like blanks.

68
00:10:03,239 --> 00:10:04,640
Hi, baby dog.

69
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:17,640
Ace, be careful. Good boy.

70
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,159
Hello?

71
00:10:27,599 --> 00:10:29,159
Well, let`s see.

72
00:10:30,039 --> 00:10:32,280
lt`s $650, utilities included.

73
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:34,520
lt`s a garage apartment.

74
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:38,960
No, no problems with the fumes.
We park our car outside.

75
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:44,760
lt`s partially furnished. There`s a bed
and a table right now, but that`s about it.

76
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:48,080
l see. Well, okay. Sorry.

77
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,159
Hi, sweetness.

78
00:10:54,919 --> 00:10:57,479
Tragedy continues to strike
around the globe...

79
00:10:57,599 --> 00:11:00,640
...as the changing
weather patterns continue.

80
00:11:01,679 --> 00:11:03,400
-Hi, honey.
-Hi.

81
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:07,280
-That`s nice.
-Thanks.

82
00:11:09,799 --> 00:11:11,200
How did it go today?

83
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:14,520
The State Supreme Court
denied my appeal.

84
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,679
-Are you kidding?
-l couldn`t believe it.

85
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:21,119
-l thought you had such a strong appeal.
-So did l.

86
00:11:22,719 --> 00:11:23,840
So did l.

87
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,760
The whole petition was based on the fact
that Jimmy`s trial lawyer was incompetent.

88
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:32,799
l`ve told you that. l thought l proved it.

89
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,400
Shit. What are you going to do?

90
00:11:37,679 --> 00:11:39,599
Appeal again. Fight it.

91
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,239
Anyway, how`s our bouncing baby boy?

92
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:45,200
Good. We had a good day.

93
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:47,159
Good.

94
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,719
l know we talked about it
and decided not to...

95
00:11:57,919 --> 00:12:00,880
...but l went to the Oaks today
and put down a deposit.

96
00:12:03,239 --> 00:12:05,599
lt only puts us on the waiting list
for four years.

97
00:12:05,719 --> 00:12:07,280
Why are you doing this?

98
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,799
l just want to be prepared.

99
00:12:10,919 --> 00:12:12,719
l want you to be realistic.

100
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:16,359
-l am realistic.
-We don`t know for sure if the baby--

101
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:21,039
l saw Dr. lnness today.
She said l`m doing perfect. No problems.

102
00:12:22,679 --> 00:12:23,719
Really?

103
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,719
This baby is going to be fine.

104
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:29,039
lt has to be.

105
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:32,200
lt has to be? What if it isn`t? Then what?

106
00:12:56,559 --> 00:12:59,000
l just don`t want to lose you, that`s all.

107
00:13:03,359 --> 00:13:04,320
Okay?

108
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:10,719
Okay.

109
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,440
Will you die for Him?

110
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,320
Will you die for Him?

111
00:15:05,159 --> 00:15:06,400
What is it?

112
00:15:08,239 --> 00:15:09,640
What`s the matter?

113
00:15:09,799 --> 00:15:11,599
l was in these rooms.

114
00:15:11,719 --> 00:15:14,280
Oh, God, l could feel it coming.

115
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,880
Death.

116
00:15:20,119 --> 00:15:23,080
lt was just a dream, Abby.
lt was just a dream.

117
00:15:27,919 --> 00:15:29,239
lt`s all right.

118
00:15:31,799 --> 00:15:33,520
lt was just a dream.

119
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,159
Russell Quinn?

120
00:16:36,919 --> 00:16:39,039
Penny Washburn. Sorry l`m late.

121
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,440
l understand you`re quite an expert
on death sentence appeals.

122
00:16:42,559 --> 00:16:43,440
So they say.

123
00:16:43,559 --> 00:16:45,280
What do you know about this case?

124
00:16:45,359 --> 00:16:48,400
So far, not much.
The kid murdered his parents?

125
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:52,359
He poured gasoline on them and
set them on fire while they were sleeping.

126
00:16:52,479 --> 00:16:55,119
l take it this is not someone
with a lot of remorse.

127
00:16:55,239 --> 00:16:57,119
His parents were brother and sister.

128
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:01,559
"Executed for the word of God"
is what he said in his signed confession.

129
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,119
Jimmy....

130
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,479
-How`s it going?
-Hello, Russell.

131
00:17:18,439 --> 00:17:22,479
This is Penny Washburn.
She`s going to help us with your case.

132
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,199
-Hello, Penny.
-Hello.

133
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,400
-Can we talk a minute?
-Yes.

134
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:44,280
Penny`s going to help me
prepare a new appeal...

135
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:46,160
...but we`ll need your help.

136
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:49,079
l told you, l do not go to hospital.

137
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,640
l can`t help you unless you let me.

138
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,760
Just talk to her,
tell her what happened, that`s all.

139
00:17:56,319 --> 00:17:57,640
No hospital.

140
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,640
Jimmy, this is important.

141
00:18:02,119 --> 00:18:05,680
lf you go to the hospital,
the doctors may find you incompetent.

142
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:10,400
Then the court will reconsider your case.
Otherwise, we don`t have anything.

143
00:18:11,959 --> 00:18:14,599
l know what is right
and l know what is wrong.

144
00:18:14,959 --> 00:18:16,680
l did nothing wrong.

145
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,079
You admitted killing your parents.

146
00:18:21,560 --> 00:18:24,439
lt was not wrong. lt was the law of God.

147
00:18:25,239 --> 00:18:26,280
Leviticus.

148
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:29,079
lsn`t murder a crime too,
in the eyes of God?

149
00:18:29,479 --> 00:18:31,680
lt is not murder to punish the guilty.

150
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,280
lncest may be against the law of God...

151
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:37,520
...but it`s the law of California
that we`re dealing with.

152
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:40,839
They`ve sentenced you to the gas chamber!
Do you want to die?

153
00:18:40,959 --> 00:18:41,839
No.

154
00:18:41,959 --> 00:18:46,000
Then go to the hospital and let the doctors
see if you knew what you were doing.

155
00:18:46,079 --> 00:18:48,719
That says l did a crime!
That it was wrong!

156
00:18:49,359 --> 00:18:53,079
lf it`ll save your life, say you`re wrong!
What is it going to matter?

157
00:18:53,199 --> 00:18:54,839
lt matters to God!

158
00:18:56,359 --> 00:18:57,680
No hospital.

159
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,359
Goodbye, Penny.

160
00:19:08,079 --> 00:19:10,400
Jimmy, think about it. Please.

161
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,599
-Hello.
-Hi.

162
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:58,119
My name is David.

163
00:19:58,400 --> 00:19:59,800
David Bannen.

164
00:20:00,079 --> 00:20:01,959
l`m here about the apartment.

165
00:20:02,079 --> 00:20:03,640
Please, come in.

166
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:12,880
Ace, get down! He usually doesn`t do this.
Go on, get down.

167
00:20:13,239 --> 00:20:15,239
lt`s okay. Hi, Ace.

168
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:16,959
Get down!

169
00:20:20,239 --> 00:20:23,880
l`m surprised. He never does this.
l`ll go get the keys.

170
00:20:26,599 --> 00:20:28,880
Would you like a towel? You`re soaked.

171
00:20:29,359 --> 00:20:31,599
lt`s terrible out there, isn`t it?

172
00:20:32,239 --> 00:20:34,239
Yes, it is.

173
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,920
lf l can just find these keys.

174
00:20:40,079 --> 00:20:41,479
Where are you from?

175
00:20:42,359 --> 00:20:44,920
All over. l`ve moved around a lot.

176
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,520
-Because of work?
-Yes.

177
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:49,199
What do you do?

178
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,880
l`m a teacher. Ancient languages.

179
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,199
Over at the university?

180
00:20:57,199 --> 00:20:59,680
l`ve been travelling for some time.

181
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:02,680
l`ve really just come back to town.

182
00:21:03,959 --> 00:21:05,439
May l have some water?

183
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,520
Sure. Let me get you a glass.

184
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:11,839
-Use the bottled water, it`s better.
-Thanks.

185
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,359
Your baby is due in February.

186
00:21:28,359 --> 00:21:29,479
The 29th.

187
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:31,719
How did you know?

188
00:21:34,599 --> 00:21:36,000
l saw your calendar.

189
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:41,359
lt`s kind of nice.
There isn`t a 29th except leap year.

190
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:43,839
Makes it special somehow.

191
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:46,439
lt is a special day.

192
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:52,079
l am getting so absent-minded.

193
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:55,239
l hope you`re not expecting
something fancy.

194
00:21:59,079 --> 00:22:00,319
This is it.

195
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,719
lt`s a bit small.

196
00:22:05,239 --> 00:22:07,119
l don`t need much room.

197
00:22:24,959 --> 00:22:26,280
l`d like it.

198
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:29,000
-lf that`s all right.
-That`s great!

199
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:33,520
l`ll discuss it with my husband,
but l`m sure it won`t be a problem.

200
00:22:33,839 --> 00:22:36,079
Call me tomorrow and l`ll let you know.

201
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:38,520
-Fine.
-We`ll talk then.

202
00:22:42,599 --> 00:22:44,479
l do hope this will work out.

203
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,400
l hope so, too.

204
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,040
l`m back.

205
00:22:53,439 --> 00:22:55,160
That didn`t take very long.

206
00:22:55,479 --> 00:22:58,920
He didn`t need much help.
About all he had was a suitcase.

207
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:03,079
But he did have
first and last month`s rent in cash.

208
00:23:05,439 --> 00:23:07,160
Did you ask him to dinner?

209
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:11,319
l did. He said, "No, thanks."
Of course, he didn`t use so many words.

210
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:16,000
The guy is out there.
He`s a little bit different.

211
00:23:16,079 --> 00:23:18,319
l don`t know, l think he`s just quiet.

212
00:23:18,479 --> 00:23:22,439
He`s quiet all right.
He doesn`t have a stereo or a television.

213
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,800
He doesn`t even want a telephone.

214
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,400
Really? That`s weird.

215
00:23:26,520 --> 00:23:29,400
What`s weird is that
he has a short-wave radio.

216
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,680
You think he`s a spy?

217
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:37,199
The spearhead of an invasion force
that will take over and bore us to death!

218
00:23:37,319 --> 00:23:39,359
You`re such a nut. Toss that up.

219
00:23:39,719 --> 00:23:43,680
-Where are you going?
-l`m sure you did a great job inviting him.

220
00:23:44,119 --> 00:23:45,520
Looks tossed to me.

221
00:25:17,239 --> 00:25:20,880
-Jesus, you scared me to death.
-You snuck up on me!

222
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,599
l was trying not to scare you.
What are you doing?

223
00:25:23,719 --> 00:25:26,040
Look at this. lsn`t this wild?

224
00:25:27,959 --> 00:25:29,439
Yeah, it is strange.

225
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:35,239
David`s in the house.
He changed his mind about dinner.

226
00:25:35,359 --> 00:25:38,000
Maybe he`d change it again
if he saw you snooping.

227
00:25:38,079 --> 00:25:39,640
l`m not snooping.

228
00:25:40,319 --> 00:25:41,640
l`m looking.

229
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:45,760
So after all that,
the senator wouldn`t even see me.

230
00:25:46,319 --> 00:25:50,599
This poor kid will die in the gas chamber
and l get this aide who tells me...

231
00:25:50,719 --> 00:25:53,280
...he doesn`t think their involvement
is appropriate.

232
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,359
Why?

233
00:25:54,479 --> 00:25:56,520
Because he`s a politician.

234
00:25:56,680 --> 00:26:01,479
He won`t get involved in anything
that could come back and bite his fat ass.

235
00:26:01,719 --> 00:26:03,920
-lt`s typical.
-lt`s typical bullshit.

236
00:26:04,599 --> 00:26:06,239
What would you do?

237
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:09,040
Me? What do you mean?

238
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:10,719
Would you stop it?

239
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:14,239
Of course l would, but l have no control.
l can`t do anything.

240
00:26:15,119 --> 00:26:16,520
Maybe you can.

241
00:26:18,920 --> 00:26:21,079
She can`t do anything, David.

242
00:26:21,199 --> 00:26:25,160
That`s what l`m saying, nobody listens
anymore. l`m the kid`s attorney...

243
00:26:25,239 --> 00:26:28,359
...and they won`t listen to me.
So they won`t listen to Abby.

244
00:26:28,439 --> 00:26:30,000
Maybe you are right.

245
00:26:31,079 --> 00:26:32,719
lt`s not up to us.

246
00:26:33,239 --> 00:26:34,719
-How about dessert?
-Please.

